const SKILL_MD_CONTENT = "---\nname: md-math-to-pdf\ndescription: Convert Markdown files containing LaTeX math formulas to beautifully rendered PDFs with perfect equation display. Uses Python (markdown + MathJax 3 + Playwright/Edge headless). Use when user asks to convert md to pdf, export markdown as pdf, render math formulas to pdf, or any request involving Markdown with LaTeX equations to PDF conversion.\nversion: 1.0.0\n---\n\n# Markdown + LaTeX Math to PDF\n\n## Overview\n\nConverts Markdown files with embedded LaTeX math formulas into PDF documents where all equations are fully rendered. The pipeline is:\n\n1. **Markdown -> HTML**: Parse markdown while preserving LaTeX formulas, embed MathJax 3 for client-side rendering\n2. **HTML -> PDF**: Use a headless browser to wait for MathJax to finish rendering, then export to PDF\n\nTwo export backends are supported (auto-detected):\n- **Playwright** (preferred): Explicitly waits for `MathJax.startup.promise`, most reliable\n- **Edge/Chrome headless** (fallback): Uses `--virtual-time-budget` to give MathJax time to render; no extra install needed on Windows\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Python 3.8+\n- Package `markdown`: `pip install markdown`\n- **Primary path**: Package `playwright`: `pip install playwright && python -m playwright install chromium`\n- **Fallback path**: Microsoft Edge or Google Chrome (pre-installed on most systems)\n\n## Conversion Steps\n\n### Step 1: Check Environment\n\nVerify `markdown` is installed. Try importing `playwright`; if unavailable, fall back to Edge/Chrome headless.\n\n```python\nimport importlib, os, sys\n\n# Check markdown\ntry:\n    import markdown\nexcept ImportError:\n    sys.exit(\"ERROR: 'markdown' package not installed. Run: pip install markdown\")\n\n# Check playwright\nHAS_PLAYWRIGHT = importlib.util.find_spec(\"playwright\") is not None\n\n# Check for Edge/Chrome fallback\nBROWSER_EXE = None\nfor candidate in [\n    r\"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft\\Edge\\Application\\msedge.exe\",\n    r\"C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft\\Edge\\Application\\msedge.exe\",\n    r\"C:\\Program Files\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\",\n    r\"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\",\n]:\n    if os.path.isfile(candidate):\n        BROWSER_EXE = candidate\n        break\n\nif not HAS_PLAYWRIGHT and not BROWSER_EXE:\n    sys.exit(\"ERROR: Neither playwright nor Edge/Chrome found. Install one.\")\n\nprint(f\"Playwright: {'available' if HAS_PLAYWRIGHT else 'not available'}\")\nprint(f\"Browser fallback: {BROWSER_EXE or 'not found'}\")\n```\n\nIf neither is available, install playwright:\n```bash\npip install playwright\npython -m playwright install chromium\n```\n\n### Step 2: Generate Conversion Script\n\nWrite the following Python script to a temp file and execute it. Replace `INPUT_FILE` and `OUTPUT_FILE` with actual paths.\n\n```python\n\"\"\"\nmd_math_to_pdf.py - Convert Markdown with LaTeX math to PDF.\nUsage: python md_math_to_pdf.py <input.md> <output.pdf>\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport markdown\n\n\ndef extract_math_and_convert(md_text):\n    \"\"\"Parse markdown while protecting LaTeX math blocks from the parser.\"\"\"\n    math_blocks = []\n    counter = [0]\n\n    def save_and_replace(match):\n        idx = counter[0]\n        math_blocks.append(match.group(0))\n        counter[0] += 1\n        return f\"MATHPH{idx:04d}ENDPH\"\n\n    # Order matters: display math before inline math\n    md_text = re.sub(r'\\\\\\[.*?\\\\\\]', save_and_replace, md_text, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    md_text = re.sub(r'\\$\\$.*?\\$\\$', save_and_replace, md_text, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    md_text = re.sub(r'(?<!\\$)\\$(?!\\$)(.+?)(?<!\\$)\\$(?!\\$)', save_and_replace, md_text, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    md_text = re.sub(r'\\\\\\(.*?\\\\\\)', save_and_replace, md_text, flags=re.DOTALL)\n\n    # Convert markdown to HTML\n    html_body = markdown.markdown(md_text, extensions=['tables', 'fenced_code', 'toc'])\n\n    # Restore math blocks\n    for i, block in enumerate(math_blocks):\n        html_body = html_body.replace(f\"MATHPH{i:04d}ENDPH\", block)\n\n    return html_body\n\n\ndef fix_image_paths(html_body, base_dir):\n    \"\"\"Convert relative image paths to absolute file:// URLs.\"\"\"\n    def replacer(m):\n        prefix = m.group(1)\n        src = m.group(2)\n        if re.match(r'\\w+://', src):\n            return m.group(0)\n        abs_path = os.path.normpath(os.path.join(base_dir, src))\n        return f'{prefix}src=\"file:///{abs_path.replace(os.sep, \"/\")}\"'\n\n    return re.sub(r'<img\\s+([^>]*?)src=\"([^\"]+)\"', replacer, html_body)\n\n\ndef wrap_with_mathjax(html_body, title=\"Document\"):\n    \"\"\"Wrap HTML body in a full document with MathJax 3 and print-ready CSS.\"\"\"\n    return f\"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"zh-CN\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<title>{title}</title>\n<script>\nwindow.MathJax = {{\n  tex: {{\n    inlineMath: [['$', '$'], ['\\\\\\\\(', '\\\\\\\\)']],\n    displayMath: [['$$', '$$'], ['\\\\\\\\[', '\\\\\\\\]']],\n    processEscapes: true,\n    processEnvironments: true,\n    packages: {{ '[+]': ['amsmath', 'amssymb', 'mhchem'] }},\n    tags: 'ams',\n  }},\n  options: {{\n    skipHtmlTags: ['script', 'noscript', 'style', 'textarea', 'pre', 'code'],\n  }},\n  startup: {{\n    pageReady: () => {{\n      return MathJax.startup.defaultPageReady().then(() => {{\n        document.body.classList.add('mathjax-done');\n      }});\n    }}\n  }}\n}};\n</script>\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\" async></script>\n<style>\n  body {{\n    font-family: \"Source Han Serif SC\", \"Noto Serif CJK SC\", \"SimSun\", \"Songti SC\",\n                 \"Latin Modern Roman\", \"Computer Modern Serif\", Georgia, serif;\n    max-width: 800px;\n    margin: 40px auto;\n    padding: 0 20px;\n    line-height: 1.8;\n    color: #222;\n    font-size: 14px;\n  }}\n  h1 {{ font-size: 1.6em; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: 6px; }}\n  h2 {{ font-size: 1.3em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 4px; margin-top: 2em; }}\n  h3 {{ font-size: 1.1em; margin-top: 1.5em; }}\n  blockquote {{\n    border-left: 4px solid #ddd; margin: 1em 0; padding: 0.5em 1em;\n    color: #555; background: #f9f9f9;\n  }}\n  hr {{ border: none; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 2em 0; }}\n  code {{ background: #f4f4f4; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em; }}\n  img {{ max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; margin: 1em auto; }}\n  table {{ border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 1em 0; }}\n  th, td {{ border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 8px 12px; text-align: left; }}\n  th {{ background: #f5f5f5; }}\n  @media print {{\n    body {{ max-width: 100%; margin: 0; padding: 15mm; font-size: 11pt; }}\n    h1, h2, h3 {{ page-break-after: avoid; }}\n    img {{ page-break-inside: avoid; }}\n  }}\n  @page {{ size: A4; margin: 20mm 18mm; }}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n{html_body}\n</body>\n</html>\"\"\"\n\n\ndef export_with_playwright(html_path, output_path):\n    \"\"\"Use Playwright to render HTML and export to PDF, waiting for MathJax.\"\"\"\n    from playwright.sync_api import sync_playwright\n\n    with sync_playwright() as p:\n        browser = p.chromium.launch(headless=True)\n        page = browser.new_page()\n        page.goto(f\"file:///{html_path.replace(os.sep, '/')}\")\n        # Wait for MathJax to finish rendering\n        page.wait_for_function(\n            \"() => document.body.classList.contains('mathjax-done')\",\n            timeout=60000\n        )\n        # Extra wait for fonts to settle\n        page.wait_for_timeout(2000)\n        page.pdf(\n            path=output_path,\n            format=\"A4\",\n            margin={\"top\": \"20mm\", \"bottom\": \"20mm\", \"left\": \"18mm\", \"right\": \"18mm\"},\n            print_background=True,\n        )\n        browser.close()\n    print(f\"[Playwright] PDF exported: {output_path}\")\n\n\ndef export_with_browser(html_path, output_path):\n    \"\"\"Fallback: use Edge/Chrome headless --print-to-pdf.\"\"\"\n    browser_exe = None\n    for candidate in [\n        r\"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft\\Edge\\Application\\msedge.exe\",\n        r\"C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft\\Edge\\Application\\msedge.exe\",\n        r\"C:\\Program Files\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\",\n        r\"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\",\n    ]:\n        if os.path.isfile(candidate):\n            browser_exe = candidate\n            break\n\n    if not browser_exe:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"No Edge/Chrome found for fallback export\")\n\n    file_url = f\"file:///{html_path.replace(os.sep, '/')}\"\n    cmd = [\n        browser_exe,\n        \"--headless\",\n        \"--disable-gpu\",\n        \"--no-sandbox\",\n        \"--run-all-compositor-stages-before-draw\",\n        \"--virtual-time-budget=30000\",\n        f'--print-to-pdf={output_path}',\n        \"--no-pdf-header-footer\",\n        file_url,\n    ]\n    result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=120)\n    if not os.path.isfile(output_path):\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Browser export failed: {result.stderr}\")\n    print(f\"[Browser] PDF exported: {output_path}\")\n\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) < 3:\n        print(\"Usage: python md_math_to_pdf.py <input.md> <output.pdf>\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    input_file = sys.argv[1]\n    output_file = sys.argv[2]\n\n    if not os.path.isfile(input_file):\n        sys.exit(f\"Input file not found: {input_file}\")\n\n    # Read markdown\n    with open(input_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        md_text = f.read()\n\n    # Convert\n    base_dir = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(input_file))\n    title = os.path.splitext(os.path.basename(input_file))[0]\n\n    html_body = extract_math_and_convert(md_text)\n    html_body = fix_image_paths(html_body, base_dir)\n    html_full = wrap_with_mathjax(html_body, title)\n\n    # Write intermediate HTML\n    html_path = os.path.splitext(output_file)[0] + \".html\"\n    with open(html_path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        f.write(html_full)\n    print(f\"HTML generated: {html_path}\")\n\n    # Export to PDF\n    import importlib\n    if importlib.util.find_spec(\"playwright\") is not None:\n        export_with_playwright(html_path, output_file)\n    else:\n        export_with_browser(html_path, output_file)\n\n    # Report\n    size_kb = os.path.getsize(output_file) / 1024\n    print(f\"Done! PDF size: {size_kb:.1f} KB\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n### Step 3: Execute Conversion\n\nRun the script with the user's input and output paths:\n\n```bash\npython <script_path>/md_math_to_pdf.py \"<input.md>\" \"<output.pdf>\"\n```\n\n### Step 4: Verify Output\n\nAfter conversion, verify the PDF:\n\n```python\nimport pypdf, os\ndoc = pypdf.PdfReader(\"<output.pdf>\")\nprint(f\"Pages: {len(doc.pages)}\")\nprint(f\"Size: {os.path.getsize('<output.pdf>') / 1024:.1f} KB\")\n# Spot-check: extract text from first page to confirm content\ntext = doc.pages[0].extract_text()\nprint(f\"First page preview:\\n{text[:300]}\")\n```\n\nCheck that:\n- Page count is reasonable for the document length\n- Text extraction returns content (not empty pages)\n- Math symbols appear in extracted text (e.g., integral signs, fractions)\n\n## Key Technical Notes\n\n### Why Math Blocks Must Be Protected\n\nThe Python `markdown` parser will mangle LaTeX syntax. For example, `$x^2$` might be interpreted as emphasis markers, and `\\[...\\]` could confuse the parser. The solution is to extract all math blocks before parsing, replace them with inert placeholders, then restore them after HTML conversion so MathJax can process them.\n\n### Why Playwright Waits Matter\n\nMathJax renders asynchronously: it downloads web fonts, parses LaTeX, and injects SVG/HTML into the DOM. Playwright's `wait_for_function` on `document.body.classList.contains('mathjax-done')` ensures all formulas are rendered before the PDF snapshot is taken. This is the exact fix that VSCode plugins like Markdown PDF and MPE are missing.\n\n### Edge/Chrome `--virtual-time-budget` Explained\n\nThe `--virtual-time-budget=30000` flag gives the headless browser 30 seconds of simulated time. This allows MathJax's async rendering pipeline (CDN fetch + LaTeX processing + font loading) to complete before the PDF is generated. It's less precise than Playwright's explicit wait but works well in practice.\n\n### MathJax Configuration\n\nThe embedded MathJax 3 config enables:\n- **amsmath / amssymb**: For `\\boxed`, `\\tag`, `cases`, `\\dfrac`, etc.\n- **mhchem**: For chemical equations like `\\ce{H2O}`\n- **tags: 'ams'**: Automatic equation numbering\n- **Inline delimiters**: `$...$` and `\\(...\\)`\n- **Display delimiters**: `$$...$$` and `\\[...\\]`\n\n### Chinese Font Support\n\nThe CSS font stack includes Source Han Serif SC, Noto Serif CJK SC, and SimSun for proper Chinese character rendering. On systems without these fonts, MathJax's CHTML output may fall back to system fonts.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Problem | Solution |\n|---------|----------|\n| Playwright browser not installed | `python -m playwright install chromium` |\n| Formulas appear as raw LaTeX in PDF | MathJax CDN unreachable; check network or use local MathJax |\n| Chinese characters show as boxes | Install Source Han Serif or Noto CJK fonts |\n| Image not found in PDF | Ensure image paths are relative to the .md file location |\n| Playwright timeout | Increase timeout in `wait_for_function` (default 60s) |\n| Browser fallback fails | Check Edge/Chrome is installed; try `--virtual-time-budget=60000` |\n| Large document is slow | MathJax processing scales with formula count; consider splitting |\n";
